martin fabinyi is an australian film and television producer and director , songwriter and screenwriter and has written books on the local rock music scene .   he was the chief executive officer of mushroom pictures from its formation in 1995 to 2009 .   his film projects include the features chopper ( 2000 ) , gettin ' square ( 2003 ) and macbeth ( 2006 ) .   in 2001 , fabinyi was named one of the top ten international producers to watch by variety and one of the most influential people in the australian film industry by screen international magazine .   in 1978 , fabinyi and composer , cameron allan , formed the regular records label , initially for releases by pop and r&b band , mental as anything , which were soon managed by his younger brother , jeremy .